an class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-family: 'Courier New'; =
font-size: 13px; "><a =
href=3D"http://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=3Dlondial2008">http://w=
ww.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=3Dlondial2008</a></span></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US">=A0Before submitting you must =
register with the website and receive a password by email; please do =
this well ahead of your submission, since email is sometimes unreliable. =
You will also need to fill out a web form with the author details and =
type in (or paste) a plain-text version of your abstract (200 words), in =
addition to uploading your paper.</span></p><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
lang=3D"EN-US">=A0<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
lang=3D"EN-US">The actual paper should be an anonymous PDF file, 8 pages =
long (including data, tables, figures, and references), A4 paper size, =
11pt Times font, 2.5 cm (1 inch) margins, 2-column format. Include a =
one-paragraph abstract of the entire work (about 200 words). You may =
find it convenient to use the style files provided by=A0<span =
style=3D"color: black; ">ACL 2007. Please specify whether your paper is =
for the DSiJA.<span>=A0</span><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US">Multiple submissions by the =
same author or group of authors are allowed, but each person may only =
give one oral presentation at the workshop.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US">=A0<o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US">We will have a separate =
submission of late-breaking system demonstrations and ongoing project =
descriptions, to be presented in a poster session during the workshop. =
Late-breaking submissions will be two pages long; they will not be =
refereed, but evaluated for relevance only by the program committee =
chairs. Submission of late-breaking abstracts will be allowed only after =
review of the main session papers has concluded. The deadline for =
late-breaking submissions is 30<sup>th</sup>=A0April =
2008.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
lang=3D"EN-US">=A0<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
